Biography Genre: Electronic Years Active: '00s, '10s Magnus August Høiberg, known as Cashmere Cat, is a downtempo/abstract electronic music producer and turntablist from Halden, Norway. From 2006 through 2009, under the alias Final, he represented his country at the DMC World DJ Championship. He branched into production and remix work; among his most notable early output is Wildchild (of the Lootpack)'s "Stuck in Norway," and Final remixes of tracks by Classixx and Jaga Jazzist.
